post_text:
Good Afternoon,

This is Michael Chimente, I hope that this message finds all of your family and you well. I was holding out hope that we would return to school, which would provide some normalcy for all of us. However, that does not appear to be the case. Based on all of the information that we are hearing/receiving from CDE, it appears that we will be physically closed for the rest of this school year. I appreciate all that you are doing helping us to maintain and continue the education for all of our students. Once the "shelter-in-place" ban is lifted, we will schedule Scholarship Night, Graduation, and in conjunction with the Sober Grad Foundation, a celebration for our Seniors.

Thank you and stay well,
Michael Chimente
Superintendent

“Good Afternoon,

Starting this Wednesday, April 1st, 2020 a weeks worth of meals will be provided each Wednesday until further notice, to Bret Harte UHSD students that place meal requests no later than Tuesday afternoon for Wednesday pickup.

Please either call 209-736-8340 or email Chris Fouts at cfouts@bhuhsd.k12.ca.us to place your order. Include the number of Bret Harte District student meals needed and the preferred site for pick up.

The sites for pick up will be in the parking lots of: Copper Elementary, Bret Harte High School (by the theater), Michelson Elementary, Avery Middle School, and Hazel Fischer Elementary between the hours of 10:00 AM to 11:00 AM.

Thank you, stay well.”

post_text:
"With the anticipated PG&E Safety Power Shutoff, Bret Harte Union High School District would like to remind students and parents of the district's policy.
• If power is shut off in our communities, but the campus still has power school will operate as normal.
• If the power outage impacts the school, school will be closed.
• If the power outage occurs during the school day, we will make every effort to stay in session and release at normal time.
Information will be sent via BHUHSD message dialer, posted on the district website's bhuhsd-ca.schoolloop.com, mymotherlode.com, thepinetree.net, KKBN 93.5 and STAR 92.7.

Parents are encouraged to check their parent portal and verify that your contact information is correct.

For more information on PG&E Safety Power Shutoff go to the PG&E’s website.

Thank you for your understanding during these uncertain times."

- Michael Chimente, Superintendent

In regards to scheduled Athletic events for Thursday, October 10 and Friday, October 11, please stay tuned to the Bret Harte Athletics' pages on Facebook and Instagram. Thank you

workshop is only offered every two years. For more information, visit Mrs. Millar in the office.

shared_text:
California Landmark Foundation is in Altaville, California.
January 13, 2019 at 2:41 PM · Altaville, CA ·

CALIFORNIA HISTORICAL LANDMARK #0288 ALTAVILLE - The history of Altaville is closely identified with that of Angels Camp. Altaville has been the foundry town of Calaveras County since D. D. Demerest established a foundry there in 1854. Most of the stamp mills and a large part of the mining machinery erected in Calaveras and Tuolumne Counties were built at the Altaville Foundry. A brick schoolhouse was built at Altaville in 1858 and the townsite was established in 1873.

Location:
SR 49 at Murphy's Grade Rd. (Main Street and Mrphy's Grade Road, Angels Camp, CA.

Mike Borean
December 15, 2018 at 7:25 PM ·

Bret Harte wrestler Kodiak Stephens takes the gold at the Mike Tamana tournament in Modesto today. In five matches, he tech’ed two, pinned one, one opponent was injured and forfeited, he beat his opponent in the championship match 3-0. This opponent was a state qualifier last year. Kodi’s cumulative score for the tournament was 57-7. No offensive points were scored against him.

Great job Kodi!!

FFA Floriculture Team won the California State Championship last Saturday in San Luis Obispo. They competed against over 50 teams in the state. The team members are:

Madelyn Ruff-4th high individual in the state
Zoe Hartsinck
Kaegen Moore
Jessica Godospeed

They will be traveling to Indianapolis, Indiana in the Fall to compete against the first place teams of every other state.

The Bret Harte boys golf team finished

league season undefeated with a record of 12-0.

Nick Kristoff was named league MVP and

Mason Davis was named All-League.

Nick Kristoff, Mason Davis, Connor Barajas,

Kallen Dente, Evan Shields, Nathan Vickerman

and BJ Singh.

Next match will be Monday, May 7th for

Divisional championship at Castle Oaks Golf Course.

Bret Harte Theater
April 12, 2018 at 10:30 AM ·

Ticket info: http://addamsbh.bpt.me/

Bret Harte Drama proudly presents The Addams Family Musical: School Edition in the Dr. Elliott A. Smart Performing Arts Center, April 19-21 at 7pm.
The Addams Family features an original story, and its every fathers nightmare. Wednesday Addams, the ultimate princess of darkness, has grown up and fallen in love with a sweet, smart young man from a respectable family a man her parents have never met. And if that werent upsetting enough, Wednesday confides in her father and begs him not to tell her mother. Now, Gomez Addams must do something hes never done before keep a secret from his beloved wife, Morticia. Everything will change for the whole family on the fateful night they host a dinner for Wednesdays normal boyfriend and his parents.
